      "pos": [
        1860,
        1899
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The remaining exercises in the tutorial are written to reference the Adventure Works sample databases, but you can also choose to skip this exercise and work with your own data sources instead.",
      "pos": [
        1900,
        2093
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Here are the steps to install the Adventure Works.",
      "pos": [
        2094,
        2144
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Install the Adventure Works 2014 OLTP and Data Warehouse databases",
      "pos": [
        2150,
        2216
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Adventure Works OLTP database supports standard online transaction processing scenarios for a fictitious bicycle manufacturer (Adventure Works Cycles) including Manufacturing, Sales, and Purchasing.",
      "pos": [
        2218,
        2420
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Adventure Works DW database demonstrates how to build a data warehouse.",
      "pos": [
        2421,
        2496
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The databases are located at http://msftdbprodsamples.codeplex.com/ and can be installed by following the steps in [How to install the Adventure Works 2014 Sample Databases].",
      "pos": [
        2498,
        2672
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this exercise you installed the Adventure Works sample databases that are used in the remaining exercises.",
      "pos": [
        2674,
        2783
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you chose to skip this exercise and to use your own enterprise data sources, please be prepared to remember names, tags, and other metadata.",
